title: Tell HN: At least one ChatGPT submission on nearly every page of HN
text:
About 3,000+ to 5,000+ submissions, 30 per page, comprise HN's "live" content. That is, submissions currently accepting comments.

At present, there is at least one submission concerning "ChatGPT" on nearly every page. If there is no ChatGPT reference on a given page, then there is almost surely a submission relating to "AI", particularly "OpenAI".

Even the most popular headline stories running in the mainstream media, the ones some readers no doubt get tired of reading about, do not get that level of repetitive coverage on HN.

I express no opinion on the matter. I leave such opinions to HN commenters. These are simply observations.

Help with Android Settings
text:
Wondering if the HN collective can help me work out something. My searches are failing.

I have a Nokia Android with Android 12.

Not long ago it updated so the screen I see before the lock screen has just 4 big numbers (the time) and an emergency call button.

Anybody know if I can configure a date for that screen.

It drives me crazy that I have to unlock the phone to see the date.

Update: I don't have the option for double line clock in this blog post. But I see in the screen shot they have the date.

https://nerdschalk.com/android-12-how-to-change-lock-screen-clock/
